<tr><td class="row1" align=right valign=top><input type="radio" name="fileName" value="bannerLeft" checked></td><td class="row1"><em>Use as Left Banner</em>: The left banner is an image that appears above the buttons (view, edit, etc.) on the left side; if no image is used, the name of the first page will appear there instead. The left banner is a great way to give your site a custom look. To delete a left banner image, go to <a class="internal" href="<?toUpload?>">uploads</a> and delete the corresponding file (<tt>bannerLeft.gif</tt>, <tt>bannerLeft.jpg</tt>, or <tt>bannerLeft.png</tt>).</td></tr><tr><td class="row2" align=right valign=top><input type="radio" name="fileName" value="bannerRight"></td><td class="row2"><em>Use as Right Banner</em>: The right banner is an image that appears above the buttons (view, edit, etc.) on the right side. To delete a right banner image, go to <a class="internal" href="<?toUpload?>">uploads</a> and delete the corresponding file (<tt>bannerRight.gif</tt>, <tt>bannerRight.jpg</tt>, or <tt>bannerRight.png</tt>).</td></tr><tr><td class="row1" align=right valign=top><input type="radio" name="fileName" value="background"></td><td class="row1"><em>Use as Background</em>: The background is an image that will tile the background of the page(s). To delete a background image, go to <a class="internal" href="<?toUpload?>">uploads</a> and delete the corresponding file (<tt>background.gif</tt>, <tt>background.jpg</tt>, or <tt>background.png</tt>).</td></tr>